ew post to Get Your Attention.<br>
<br>
2 Ragefire's have been lost now. One to stupidity, and one to Killstealers.<br>
<br>
Throughout this time, I have only seen a couple of Ministry of Steel, once or twice a few other Fed people alone and once Lachadan actually help us camp this.<br>
<br>
The point of the Federation is to allow small guilds to come together to do larger things.  Well cleric epics are larger things, and lead to larger things. I ask that you help us a bit more, and show a bit more support.  <br>
<br>
Yes Rage camp is boring, yes it's not likely to pop in the first couple of days, but you want rezzes?  you want quick CR's on raids? Then Help Us, ffs. <p><img src="http://www.tc.umn.edu/~grae0019/GotrikSig1.jpg "></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ubendieq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BendiEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#70DB93>(6/28/02 8:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> a honorable suggestion</span><hr size=1> Personally, I offer the following suggestion<br>
<br>
LoLF is known for its honor and integrity. Or, for the most part it is anyway. I say that whether we are successful or not on the third spawn of Ragefire, that we bow out of the camp, and rotate our names to the back of the list.<br>
<br>
From a practical standpoint, Legion nerves are shot to hell from the strain. <br>
<br>
From a public relations standpoint, it shows respect toward the other guilds on this list, who are bound to be chomping at the bit for their spawns. <br>
<br>
While it would not be fair to us (LoLF/LoOF) in many respects to do this, it would be nicely perceived. We are a guild of *niceness first*. <br>
<br>
Thats my perspective, anyway.<br>
<br>
P.S - I'm going to reinstall EQ, and get back in game for tomorrow night, to offer to bot Dopy and Kosak both from 7pm EST Saturday night, to 9am EST sunday morning. That will give both sets of folks a nice stretch of R&amp;R. I have 3 comps, and a very comfortable chair, so I can keep an eye on them, and play games, read a book whatever.<br>
<br>
Bendi Witherspoon<br>
